- Implement `StatusBadge.tsx`:
  - Props: `{ status: "auto_filled" | "needs_review" | "empty" }`.
  - Render small inline badge with:
    - Auto-filled: green badge, text "Auto-filled" and optionally icon.
    - Needs review: yellow/amber badge, text "Needs review".
    - Empty: gray badge, text "Empty".
  - Provide CSS hook classes: `status-badge`, `status-auto`, `status-review`, `status-empty`.
- Implement a utility to determine status based on field value and metadata:
  ```ts
  function getFieldStatus(fieldName: keyof StoryBrief, brief: StoryBrief): FieldStatus {
    const value = (brief as any)[fieldName];
    if (value == null || value === "" || (Array.isArray(value) && value.length === 0)) {
      return "empty";
    }
    if (brief.auto_filled_fields?.includes(fieldName as string)) {
      return "auto_filled";
    }
    // Optionally treat some as needs_review if not auto-filled
    return "needs_review";
  }
  ```
